  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Lament Over the Land'
      title: A Lament Over the Land
      number: 1
      content: ' The word of Yahweh that came to Joel son of Pethuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear this, O elders, and give ear, all the inhabitants of the land.
        Has this happened in your days? Or the days of your ancestors? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Tell it to your children, and your children to their children, and
        their children to the following generation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What the cutting locust left, the swarming locust has eaten. What
        the swarming locust left, the hopping locust has eaten. And what the hopping
        locust left, the destroying locust has eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Wake up, drunkards, and weep! Wail, all drinkers of wine, over the
        new wine, for it is cut off from your mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Because a nation has invaded my land, strong and beyond counting. 
        Its teeth are the teeth of a lion, and its fangs are those of a lioness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It has made my vine a desolation, and my fig tree a completely splintered
        stump. It has stripped them bare and thrown them down; their branches have
        turned white. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Lament like a virgin girded in sackcloth for the husband of her youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The offering and libation are withheld from the house of Yahweh.
        The priests mourn, the ministers of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The field is destroyed; the earth mourns because the grain is destroyed,
        the new wine dries up, the olive oil languishes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Be ashamed, farmers; Wail, vinedressers, over the wheat and over
        the barley, because the harvest of the field is ruined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The vine withers and the fig tree droops. The pomegranate tree, and
        also the palm tree, the apple tree \u2014all the trees of the field\u2014are
        dried up. Indeed, joy is dried up among the sons of men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Gird yourselves and lament, O priests! Wail, O ministers of the altar!
        Come spend the night in sackcloth, O ministers of my God, because offering
        and libation are withheld from the house of your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Solemnize a fast! Call an assembly! Gather the elders, all of the
        inhabitants of the land in the house of Yahweh your God, and cry out to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ah! For the day! For the day of Yahweh is near. It will come like
        destruction from Shaddai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Is not food cut off before our eyes, from the house of our God, joy
        and gladness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The seeds shrivel under their clods; the storehouses are desolate.
        The grain storage places are destroyed because grain has dried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'How the beasts groan; the herds of cattle wander around because there
        is no pasture for them; the flocks of sheep are in distress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'To you, O Yahweh, I cry out, because fire has devoured the pastures
        of the desert, and flames burned all the trees of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Also, the beasts of the field long for you, because the courses of
        water are dried up, and fire has devoured the pastures of the desert. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Day of Yahweh is Near'
      title: The Day of Yahweh is Near
      number: 1
      content: "Blow the trumpet in Zion, and sound the alarm on my holy mountain! 
        Let all the inhabitants of the land tremble, for the day of Yahweh is coming
        \u2014it is indeed near. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A day of darkness and gloom, a day of cloud and thick darkness, like
        the dawn spreads on the mountains, a great and strong army! There has been
        nothing like it from old, and after it nothing will be again for generations
        to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Before them a fire devours, and behind them a flame burns. Like the
        garden of Eden is the land before them,  and after them it is like a desolate
        desert, and nothing can escape them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Like the appearance of horses is their appearance, and like horsemen
        they run; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'like the sound of chariots on the tops of the mountains, they leap
        about; like the sound of a flame of fire devouring stubble; like a strong
        army arranged in rows for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From before them nations writhe, all faces turn pale.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They run like mighty warriors,  they scale the wall like men of war;
        each goes on its own way, and they do not swerve from their paths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They do not jostle one another;  each goes on its own trail; and
        through the falling weapons,  they are not halted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the city they rush forth; on the walls they run. Into the houses
        they climb up; through the windows they enter like a thief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Before them the earth quakes; the heavens tremble; the sun and the
        moon grow dark, and the stars have withheld their splendor '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 11
      content: 'And Yahweh utters his voice before his army, because his encampment
        is very large; strong is the one who carries out his decree, for great is
        the day of Yahweh and exceedingly fearful. Who can endure it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd even now,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Creturn to me with
        all your heart, with fasting, and weeping, and wailing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Rend your hearts and not your garments, and return to Yahweh your
        God, because he is gracious and compassionate, slow to anger and great in
        loyal love, and relenting from harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who knows whether he will turn and relent, and leave a blessing behind
        him, an offering and a libation, for Yahweh your God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Blow the trumpet in Zion, sanctify a fast, call an assembly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'gather the people, consecrate the assembly; assemble the elders,
        gather the children, even those who are breast-feeding; let the bridegroom
        come out from his private room, and the bride from her canopy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Response and Promise of Yahweh'
      title: The Response and Promise of Yahweh
      number: 17
      content: "Between the colonnade and the altar, let the priests, the ministers
        of Yahweh, weep. And let them say, \u201CTake pity, Yahweh, on your people.
        Do not make your inheritance a reproach, a byword among the nations. Why
        should they say among the nations, \u2018Where is their God?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Yahweh became jealous for his land and took pity on his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Yahweh answered and said to his people, \u201CLook at me, I am
        sending to you grain, new wine, and olive oil, and you will be satisfied
        by it. I will not give you over any more as a disgrace among the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The northerners  I will remove from you; I will drive them to a desert
        and desolate land, its front to the eastern sea, and its rear into the western
        sea; its stench and odor will rise up because he has done great things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do not fear, O land, rejoice and be glad, because Yahweh has done
        great things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do not fear, wild animals of the field, because the pastures of the
        desert have put forth new green shoots, because the tree has produced its
        fruit, the fig tree and the vine have yielded their produce. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Be glad, O children of Zion, be glad and rejoice in Yahweh your God,
        because he has given for you the autumn rains for your righteousness,  and
        he has poured down for you rainwater, the autumn and spring rains, as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The threshing floors will be full with grain, and the vats will overflow
        with new wine and olive oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I will repay you the years that the locust has eaten, the hopper,
        the destroyer, and the cutter, my mighty troops that I sent against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And you will eat abundantly and be satisfied, and praise the name
        of Yahweh your God, who has dealt with you wondrously.  My people will never
        be ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Yahweh\u2019s Spirit Poured Out"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Spirit Poured Out"
      number: 27
      content: 'And you will know that I am in the midst of Israel, and I am Yahweh,
        your God, and there is no other. My people will never be ashamed again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: ' And it will happen afterward thus: I will pour out my Spirit on
        all flesh, and your sons and your daughters will prophesy, and your elders
        will dream dreams; your young men shall see visions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And also on the male slaves and on the female slaves, I will pour
        out my Spirit in those days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And I will set wonders in the heavens, and on earth, blood and fire
        and columns of smoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sun will be changed to darkness, and the moon to blood, before
        the coming of the great and awesome day of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And it will happen\u2014everyone who calls on the name of Yahweh
        will be rescued, because on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem there will be those
        who escape, as Yahweh said, and among the survivors whom Yahweh is calling. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on the Nations"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on the Nations"
      number: 1
      content: ' For look! In those days, and in that time, when I will return the
        fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will gather all the nations, and I will bring them down to the
        valley of Jehoshaphat, and I will argue a case against them there concerning
        my people and my inheritance Israel whom they have scattered among the nations,
        and my land that they have divided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For my people they cast lots, and they traded the male child for
        the prostitute, and the female child they sold for wine and they drank it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What are you to me, O Tyre and O Sidon, and all of the regions of
        Philistia? Are you repaying to me what is deserved? If you are recompensing
        me, I will return swiftly and quickly what you deserve on your head! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For you have taken my silver and my gold, and my beautiful treasures
        you have carried into your temples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the sons of Judah and Jerusalem you sold to the sons of the Greeks,
        in order to remove them from their border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Look! I am rousing them from the place where you have sold them,
        and I will return what you deserve on your head! '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Yahweh\u2019s Judgment in the Valley of Jehoshaphat"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Judgment in the Valley of Jehoshaphat"
      number: 8
      content: 'I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hand of the children
        of Judah, and they will sell them to the Sabeans and to a nation far away,
        for Yahweh has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Proclaim this among the nations: Prepare for war!  Stir up the mighty
        warriors; let them approach and come up; let all the men of war approach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Beat your cutting tools of iron into swords and your pruning hooks
        into spears; let the weakling say, \u2018I am a mighty warrior!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Hurry and come, all the nations, from all around, and gather yourselves
        there. Bring down your mighty warriors, O Yahweh! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let the nations be roused and let them come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat,
        for there I will sit to judge all the nations from all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Send forth the sickle, for the harvest is ripe! Go tread, for the
        winepress is full! The vats overflow, because their evil is great! '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Commotion, commotion in the valley of decision! For the day of Yahweh
        is near in the valley of decision! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sun and the moon grow dark, and the stars have withheld their
        splendor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Yahweh roars from Zion; from Jerusalem he utters his voice, and
        the heavens and the earth shake. But Yahweh is a refuge for his people, and
        a protection for the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you will know that I, Yahweh your God, am dwelling in Zion, my
        holy mountain. And Jerusalem will be a place of holiness, and strangers will
        pass through it no longer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And it will happen on that day; the mountains will drip new wine,
        and the hills will flow with milk, and all the channels of Judah will flow
        with water. A spring from the house of Yahweh will come forth, and it will
        water the valley of Acacia Trees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Egypt will become a desolation, and Edom will become a desolate desert, 
        because of the violence they did against the children of Judah, in whose
        land they have shed innocent blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Judah will be inhabited forever, and Jerusalem for all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I will cleanse their bloodguilt that I did not cleanse,  for Yahweh
        is dwelling in Zion. '
      comments: []
